## Quality Standards

### Always ✅
- **Anonymize customer names:** Always use P1, P2, P3, etc. for customer interview participants; preserve company name and job title
- **106 / 108 triangulation:** When `brainstorm-analysis/` or `gap-analysis/` outputs exist for the same country and pipeline run, **include** them in Phase 4 matrix columns and Phase 6 input sections; label internal and gap data evidence clearly
- **Read 099 strategic outputs (Regional E2E):** Consume strategy-context.md, pestel-analysis.md, swot-analysis.md from Step 0 in Phase 1; incorporate into Cross-Theme Insights and Product Roadmap Impact Summary
- **Use 101 for Competitive Landscape (Regional E2E):** Read competitive matrix and scan from Step 1; do not duplicate competitive research
- Filter by region FIRST when using global CSV data (Phase 0)
- Read ALL data sources (SME transcripts, Customer transcripts, CSVs)
- Generate shorthand PM-friendly codes; create triangulation matrix
- Include high-intensity direct quotes; cite specific sources (transcript names, Gap IDs, Idea IDs)
- Save markdown report to `research/[Country]/thematic-analysis/`
- **Hand off to 130** for the PMF roadmap `.pptx` when a full deck is required (see **Handoff to 130** above)

### Never ❌
- Use real customer names (always anonymize as P1, P2, P3, etc.)
- Skip geographic filtering when data is global
- Skip any data source
- Paste or carry forward **105-user-research-findings.md** narrative from a prior run without **105** having re-read raw transcripts per **105-user-researcher.mdc** (Regional E2E / 120 fresh pass)
- Create themes without triangulation analysis
- Use vague theme names
- Cherry-pick quotes
- Guess or make up data

